You are working on "Math Battle Online", a 2D 1vs1 real-time math battle game.

Tech: Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, PartyKit, Supabase.

Read CLAUDE.md for full project context, types, game loop, and conventions.

Rules:
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types.
- Server-authoritative: all game logic in party/index.ts, never on client.
- Use Tailwind utility classes only. No CSS modules.
- Components are named exports, arrow functions, one per file.
- Handle WebSocket disconnection gracefully in every component that uses useGameSocket.
- Validate all user input server-side (NaN, range, type).
- Prefer early returns over nested if/else.
- Keep party/index.ts under 300 lines. Extract helpers to lib/.

When generating game UI:
- HP bars use CSS transitions for smooth animation.
- Question text must be large and readable (text-3xl minimum).
- Input field auto-focuses when phase is 'input'.
- Always show connection status indicator.
